title: [Old Noralgar Road, Prairie]
description: The walls of grass bordering the faltering highway have grown to the height of a giantman. More and more, branches in its progress are a thing to dread, carrying the risk of becoming lost in the undulating ocean.  At this juncture, the main road appears to run east and west, for the other turn-offs quickly dwindle into the sward.
paths: Obvious paths: north, east, southeast, west
